    "comment": "Rationale: In this paper, the authors copurified VAMP-1 together with synaptic vesicles that were isolated from electric-organ tissue of Torpedo california (Fig. 3). Moreover, they used partial proteolysis by trypsin to show that Vamp1 is an integral membrane protein of synaptic vesicles (Fig. 4)\n\n5/2/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: T. californica were kept undisturbed for 3 days before use. Animals were anesthetized by addition of tricaine to the seawater at a final concentration of 0.25 g/liter. Electric-organ tissue was removed and quickfrozen in liquid nitrogen.\n\n20/6/2018 Frank\n- uniprot accesion selected following blast (100% match) against protein sequence listed in Figure 1B.",
